The paper is about natural language processing, specifically about representing words and sentences. This topic falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a novel representation model that involves projecting dense word vectors into a higher dimensional space and favoring a highly sparse and binary representation of word vectors. This approach involves optimization and machine learning techniques, which are common in sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the potential applications of the proposed model in image captioning, which is a task that involves both natural language processing and computer vision (cs.CV).
